## Bandit Level 13 → Level 14

**Challenge:** The password for the next level is stored in /etc/bandit_pass/bandit14 and can only be read by user bandit14. For this level, you don’t get the next password, but you get a private SSH key that can be used to log into the next level. Look at the commands that logged you into previous bandit levels, and find out how to use the key for this level.

**Solution:**
```bash
scp -P 2220 bandit13@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:/home/bandit13/sshkey.private .
chmod 600 sshkey.private
ssh -i sshkey.private  bandit14@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p2220
cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit14

```

**Explanation:** 
`scp -P 2220 bandit13@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:/home/bandit13/sshkey.private .` execute thei commmand from your local host to download the ssh key to the current directory.
`chmod 600 sshkey.private` as to use the sshkey the group and others should have no permission use this comand.
`ssh -i sshkey.private  bandit14@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p2220` this will use the ssh key to ogin and should not ask for a password.
`cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit14` once in user bandit 14 this command can beviewed to see the password.


**What I learned:** `scp` allows you to download files remotely if authenticated.
